...News API Project

<!-- Description -->

The News API Project is a simple web application that allows users to search for news articles using a keyword. The application dynamically fetches and displays news articles based on user input.

<!-- Features -->

Responsive navigation bar with a search input field.

Users can enter a keyword to fetch related news articles.

News articles are displayed dynamically on the page.

Styled using external CSS for a clean UI.

<!-- Technologies Used -->

HTML5

CSS3

JavaScript (DOM Manipulation & Fetch API)

News API (or any API used to fetch news articles)

<!-- File Structure -->

index.html - Main HTML file containing the structure of the webpage.

Search-news.css - External stylesheet for styling the application.

Search-news.js - JavaScript file responsible for fetching and displaying news articles.

<!-- How to Use -->

Open index.html in a web browser.

Enter a keyword in the search bar and click the 'Search' button.

The application fetches and displays relevant news articles dynamically.

<!-- Setup Instructions -->

Clone the repository:

git clone <repository_url>

Navigate to the project directory:

cd news-api-project

Open index.html in your preferred web browser.

<!-- Future Enhancements -->

Add pagination for displaying more news articles.

Implement filters for news categories (e.g., sports, politics, technology).

Improve UI/UX with better styling and animations.

